Text: Inventory Collected from CNSusan BaileyOUHOUOECT you are probably aware your department has been selected to participate in Project GEM Global Enron Migration for the rollout of Windows In preparation for this rollout it is imperative that we gather information about your workstation and the applications you use To begin this data collection we have automated the process and your system has just been inventoried Once this information is received we will be working with your department coordinator Sheri Cromwell to consolidate this information to ensure this transition is as smooth as possible The GEM team would like to thank you for your participation If you have any questions please call Lee Steele at

Windows Rollout SurveyGEM wants to hear from you Your workstation has recently been upgraded to Windows Our goal is to establish a common global infrastructure that provides you with a stable and robust computing platfor m for emerging technologies This innovation through standardization also validates Enrons status as an Innovative Technology Leader Ad ditionally we are committed to providing the highest standard of customer service resolving IT issues promptly and professionally while exceeding the custom er s expectations Your feedback is key to our success in knowing how well we have performed in meeting these goals as well as where we need to improve f or future upgrades Please help us with this process by taking a few minutes to complete this survey about your recent experience with the Windows upgrade Please click Survey Thanks in advance for your participation
